This paper is primarily focused on machine learning and neural networks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with distributed computing and communication, which could place it in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The use of profiling traces and synthetic execution traces suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of stochastic gradient descent (SGD) and the investigation of data transmission policies suggest that the paper could also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the prediction and optimization of training throughput could also place the paper in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
